JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 1
IS  - 1
SP  - 3
EP  - 40
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article develops a theory in which concentrated-trading patterns arise endogenously as a result of the strategic behavior of liquidity traders and informed traders. Our results provide a partial explanation for some of the recent empirical findings concerning the patterns of volume and price variability in intraday transaction data.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/1.1.3
ER  - 



