TY  - JOUR
AU  - Dybvig, Phillip H.
T1  - Inefficient Dynamic Portfolio Strategies or How to Throw Away a Million Dollars in the Stock Market
PY  - 1988
Y1  - 1988/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/1.1.67
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 1
IS  - 1
SP  - 67
EP  - 88
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - A number of portfolio strategies followed by practitioners are dominated because they are incompletely diversified over time. The payoff distribution pricing model is used to compute the cost of following undiversified strategies. Simple numerical examples illustrate the technique, and computer-generated examples provide realistic estimates of the cost of some typical policies, using reasonable parameter values. The cost can be substantial and should not be ignored by practitioners. A section on generalizations shows bow to extend the analysis to term structure models and other general models of returns.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/1.1.67
ER  - 



